    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nApologies if this is already implemented in some way, or there is already an issue or a PR, but I couldn't find it. \n\nIn my code, I would like to mark certain if branches as unlikely.\n\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\n```cython\nif (cython.unlikely(some_condition)):\n    # do something\n```\n\nI noticed that cython already adds `unlikely` for the branches that raise exceptions. Maybe it wouldn't be to difficult to expose a generic mechanism for user. \n\nI'm happy to try and do it myself, just want get an opinion first regarding syntax and general feasibility. Does approach with `cython.unlikely` look good? Are there any caveats?\n\n\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think this could just be done in user code with: \n\n```\ncdef extern from *:\n    cdef bint unlikely(bint val) noexcept\n    cdef bint likely(bint val) noexcept\n```\n\nIn principle Cython could expose that in a pxd file (although right now there isn't anywhere obvious to put such a file).\n\nBut that's easy enough that it probably makes more sense than making it a language feature.",
